  "prompt": "How do you pre-select a seat when booking a flight on Royal Air Maroc?",
  "response": "Royal Air Maroc offers several ways to pre-select your seat when booking a flight:\n\n**1. During the Online Booking Process:**\n\n*   When booking your flight on the Royal Air Maroc website (royalairmaroc.com), you will usually be offered the option to select your seat *after* you have chosen your flight, entered passenger details, and before you get to the payment page. Look for a step that says something like \"Seat Selection\" or \"Manage My Seats\".  This step is often visually represented as a seat map.\n*   If you don't see the option during the initial booking, try looking for it in the \"Manage Booking\" section *after* you complete the booking but before check-in.\n\n**2. Through \"Manage Booking\" on the Website:**\n\n*   Go to the Royal Air Maroc website (royalairmaroc.com).\n*   Look for a \"Manage Booking\" or \"My Trip\" section. This is usually located in the header or footer of the website.\n*   Enter your booking reference (PNR) and your last name.\n*   Once you've accessed your booking, look for an option to \"Select Seats\" or \"Change Seats.\"\n*   Follow the prompts to choose your desired seat(s).\n\n**3. Contacting Royal Air Maroc Directly:**\n\n*   **Phone:**  You can call Royal Air Maroc's customer service or reservations department.  Find the appropriate phone number for your region on their website (usually under \"Contact Us\" or \"Customer Service\").\n*   **Social Media:** Sometimes, airlines offer support through their social media channels like Facebook or Twitter. You can try sending them a direct message.\n\n**4. At Check-In:**\n\n*   You can select a seat during online check-in, which usually opens 24-48 hours before your flight.  The selection might be limited at this point, but you might still find something suitable.\n*   At the airport check-in counter, the agent can assist you with seat selection, subject to availability.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Fees:** Royal Air Maroc *may* charge a fee for seat selection, especially for preferred seats like those with extra legroom or in the front of the cabin. Standard seats may be free of charge, but this can vary based on your fare class, loyalty program status, and route. The website will show you any applicable fees before you confirm your selection.\n*   **Availability:**  Seat availability is on a first-come, first-served basis.  The earlier you select your seat, the better the chance of getting your preferred option.\n*   **Fare Class:** The fare class you book sometimes influences whether or not you can select seats for free or at all. Higher fare classes often include free seat selection.\n*   **Special Needs:** If you have special seating needs (e.g., needing a seat near the lavatory or for medical reasons), it's best to contact Royal Air Maroc directly to discuss your requirements.\n*   **Unaccompanied Minors:**  There may be specific seat allocation policies for unaccompanied minors.\n\n**In summary, the best method is usually to select your seat during the initial booking process online. If you missed it, use the \"Manage Booking\" option on the website. If all else fails, contact Royal Air Maroc directly.**\n",
